  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "8:1-20 Ezra assembles the outcasts of Israel, and the dispersed of Judah. God raised up the spirits of a small remnant to accompany him. What a pity that good men should omit a good work, for want of being spoken to!",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Punctuate as follows:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ezra 8:2. ... of the sons of David, Hattush of the sons of Shechaniah.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezra 8:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ... of the sons of David, Hattush of the sons of Shechaniah.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ezra 8:3. Of the sons of Pharosh, Zechariah ....",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezra 8:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Of the sons of Pharosh, Zechariah ....",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hattush, the descendant of David, was the grandson of Shechaniah (see marginal reference).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Most of these names Ezra 8:2-14 occur also as those of heads of families in the list of the Jews who returned with Zerubbabel Ezra 2:3-15. The Septuagint and Syriac versions supply omissions in Ezra 8:5, Ezra 8:10. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Most of these names ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezra 8:2-14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " occur also as those of heads of families in the list of the Jews who returned with Zerubbabel ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezra 2:3-15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The Septuagint and Syriac versions supply omissions in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezra 8:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezra 8:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "CHAPTER 8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ezr 8:1-14. Ezra's Companions from Babylon.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1. this is the genealogy of them that went up with me from Babylon—The number given here amounts to 1754. But this is the register of adult males only, and as there were women and children also (Ezr 8:21), the whole caravan may be considered as comprising between six thousand and seven thousand.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
